The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bhupathi loses
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bhupathi loses
                      
	Madrid: Seventh-seeded Poles Marcin Matkowski and Mariusz Fyrstenberg won their second ATP doubles title of the season on Sunday with a 6-4, 6-2 victory over fourth seeds Mahesh Bhupathi and Mark Knowles in the final of the Madrid Masters.         
	On Saturday, Bhupathi and Knowles had knocked out Jonas Bjorkman and Kevin Ullyett 6-2, 6-4 to reach the doubles final.         
	In singles, world No. 4 Andy Murray cruised to his second successive Masters Series title beating Frances Gilles Simon 6-4, 7-6.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                      
